## The N+1 Problem

The most common JPA performance killer. When you load N entities and then access a lazy collection on each one, JPA fires N additional queries.

```java
// N+1 in action
List<Author> authors = authorRepo.findAll(); // 1 query
for (Author a : authors) {
    a.getBooks().size(); // N queries — one per author!
}
// Total: 1 + N queries for N authors
```

## Fixing N+1: Fetch Strategies

### JOIN FETCH (JPQL)
```java
@Query("SELECT a FROM Author a JOIN FETCH a.books WHERE a.active = true")
List<Author> findAllWithBooks();
// Produces: SELECT a.*, b.* FROM author a JOIN book b ON ... — 1 query
```

### @EntityGraph
```java
@EntityGraph(attributePaths = {"books", "books.reviews"})
List<Author> findByActiveTrue();
// Eagerly loads books and their reviews in 1 query
```

### Batch Fetching (Hibernate)
```java
@Entity
public class Author {
    @OneToMany
    @BatchSize(size = 50) // loads books for 50 authors at a time
    private List<Book> books;
}
// Reduces N queries to N/50 queries
```

## Projections

Avoid loading full entities when you only need a few fields.

### Interface Projection
```java
public interface AuthorSummary {
    String getName();
    String getEmail();
    // Automatically mapped — no @Entity loading overhead
}

List<AuthorSummary> findByActiveTrue();
// SELECT a.name, a.email FROM author — not SELECT *
```

### DTO Projection with JPQL
```java
@Query("SELECT new com.example.AuthorDto(a.name, a.email) FROM Author a")
List<AuthorDto> findAllSummaries();
```

### Spring Data Projections with @Value (SpEL)
```java
public interface FullName {
    @Value("#{target.firstName + ' ' + target.lastName}")
    String getFullName();
}
```

## Specifications (Dynamic Queries)

```java
public class BookSpecs {
    public static Specification<Book> hasAuthor(String author) {
        return (root, query, cb) ->
            author == null ? null :
            cb.equal(root.get("author").get("name"), author);
    }

    public static Specification<Book> publishedAfter(LocalDate date) {
        return (root, query, cb) ->
            date == null ? null :
            cb.greaterThan(root.get("publishedAt"), date);
    }
}

// Combine dynamically
Specification<Book> spec = Specification
    .where(hasAuthor(filter.getAuthor()))
    .and(publishedAfter(filter.getFromDate()));

bookRepo.findAll(spec, pageable);
```
